    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-02-16T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-02-16T08:00:00-05:00" n="84"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d84">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.5531/358: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brussels</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-16T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >February 16, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 16—9:11 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Minister for Foreign Affairs informed me today that his Government is deeply
                    disappointed at turn trade negotiations have taken. He asked me to use my good
                    offices to secure another interview with the President for Forthomme in order
                    that the latter may present personally a proposal which he believes will settle
                    some of the principal difficulties.</p>
                <p>Minister declared that his Government is anxious to cooperate in every way with
                    the United States Government in an effort to reach mutually satisfactory
                    agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
